On National Vietnam War Veterans Day, President Joe Biden honors the bravery and sacrifice of all those who served in the Vietnam War. He acknowledges the impact of the war on veterans, their families, caregivers, and survivors. The president highlights the ongoing commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the Vietnam War, expressing gratitude to every veteran, family member, caregiver, and survivor affected by the war. He emphasizes that the sacrifices of Vietnam veterans mattered and made a difference. President Biden pledges to never forget the service members who lost their lives and those who remain missing and unaccounted for. He promises unwavering support and care for Vietnam veterans, as well as all veterans. The president calls upon all Americans to express gratitude and compassion towards Vietnam veterans and their families through public ceremonies and programs. The proclamation affirms the commitment to commemorate the 50th Anniversary of the Vietnam War from May 28, 2012, to November 11, 2025. President Biden signs the proclamation on March 28, 2022.